@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Bobarr" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench must
have at least 4 colours.

                             How to play?

  Gameplay is simple: click on the bar you want to move, if it is next
to the empty space, and the shape of the bar is in line with it, that
bar will move there and its former position will then be 'pressed down',
if the position was not already in that state. In the game, a horizontal
bar can move to the left or right, a vertical bar can move up or down
and a diagonal bar can move diagonally up or down, depending on which
"way" it is placed...

  To complicate or simplify your task, pick the one you prefer; a bar
that is located at the edge of the board can move to the other side if
the empty space is located at the other side, and is in line with that
bar.

  Note that you can also use the numbered keys on the numeric keypad to
move the bars, as shown below:

        7         8        9
    upper left   up    upper right

        4                  6
      left               right

        1         2        3
    lower left  down   lower right

  As you move bars, an indicator shows the percentage of bars that have
been moved.

  If you get stuck on one board, or a particular game is impossible to
complete, you can restart the game by clicking on the 'New Game' button
(or the Right-Amiga and 'N' key combination) and Bobarr will display a
new board.

  Have fun!

@endnode

